title: Top U.S. states based on milk production 2016 to 2018
summary: This grouped bar chart represents 10 different States on X-axis for 3 groups 2016, 2017, and 2018. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding SOME LABEL.
State California had the maximum SOME LABEL among all 3 groups, and it was for 2016. The minimum SOME LABEL was observed in State Washington for 2017.
In State California, 2016 had the maximum SOME LABEL and it saw the lowest in State Washington out of all 10 States.
State California and Washington had the biggest gap of 33819.0 between the highest and lowest SOME LABEL found for 2016.
